{"title": "CBC-ARS2 stimulates 3'-end maturation of multiple RNA families and favors cap-proximal processing", "pubDate": "2013", "PMCID": "", "DOI": "10.1038/nsmb.2720", "PMID": "24270878", "abstract": "The nuclear cap-binding complex (CBC) stimulates multiple steps in several RNA maturation pathways, but how it functions in humans is incompletely understood. For small, capped RNAs such as pre-snRNAs, the CBC recruits PHAX. Here, we identify the CBCAP complex, composed of CBC, ARS2 and PHAX, and show that both CBCAP and CBC-ARS2 complexes can be reconstituted from recombinant proteins. ARS2 stimulates PHAX binding to the CBC and snRNA 3'-end processing, thereby coupling maturation with export. In vivo, CBC and ARS2 bind similar capped noncoding and coding RNAs and stimulate their 3'-end processing. The strongest effects are for cap-proximal polyadenylation sites, and this favors premature transcription termination. ARS2 functions partly through the mRNA 3'-end cleavage factor CLP1, which binds RNA Polymerase II through PCF11. ARS2 is thus a major CBC effector that stimulates functional and cryptic 3'-end processing sites.", "author": [{"author": "Marie Hallais", "affiliation": ["Equipe labellis\u00e9e Ligue contre le Cancer, Institut de G\u00e9n\u00e9tique Mol\u00e9culaire de Montpellier-Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Montpellier, France."], "href": "/?term=Hallais+M&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Pontvianne", "affiliation": [], "href": "/?term=Pontvianne+F&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Peter Refsing Andersen", "affiliation": [], "href": "/?term=Andersen+PR&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Marcello Clerici", "affiliation": [], "href": "/?term=Clerici+M&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Daniela Lener", "affiliation": [], "href": "/?term=Lener+D&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Nour El Houda Benbahouche", "affiliation": [], "href": "/?term=Benbahouche+Nel+H&cauthor_id=24270878"}, {"author": "Thierry Gostan", "affiliatio